description: Report an installation issue
title: "bug: :hammer_and_wrench: "
labels:
  - ["installation", "triage"]
assignees: []
body:
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        # Thanks for taking the time to fill out this installation issue report!

        Before submitting an issue, please make sure the issue hasn't been already addressed by searching through the existing and past [issues](https://{{ organisation }}/{{ project_slug }}/issues).

        By submitting a new issue, you agree with this project's [Code of Conduct](https://{{ organisation }}/{{ project_slug }}/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

        We are also happy to accept contributions from our users by means of [pull requests](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/proposing-changes-to-your-work-with-pull-requests/about-pull-requests) üöÄ. For more details see [here](https://{{ organisation }}/{{ project_slug }}t/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).
  - type: input
    id: contact
    attributes:
      label: Contact Details
      description: How can we get in touch with you if we need more info?
      placeholder: ex. email@example.com
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: checkboxes
    id: terms
    attributes:
      label: Before submittig a new issue...
      options:
        - label: I have already searched for relevant issues.
          required: true
        - label: I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct.
          required: true
  - type: textarea
    attributes:
      label: My current environment
      description: |
        Fill if you think it is necessary. It may help us to solve the issue more quickly!

        Please run the following and paste the output below.

        ```console
        python -c "import rich; from {{ package_name }}.debug_info import gather_debug_info; rich.print(gather_debug_info())"
        ```

        For security purposes, please feel free to check and edit the output of `gather_debug_info()`.
      value: |
        <details>
        <summary>The output of `gather_debug_info()`</summary>

        ```python
        Your output of `gather_debug_info()` here
        ```
        </details>
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: textarea
    id: what-happened
    attributes:
      label: How I am installing the package
      description: |
        Paste the full commands you are trying to execute.
      value: |
        ```sh
        pip install -vvv .
        ```
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: textarea
    id: logs
    attributes:
      label: Relevant log output
      description: |
        Please copy and paste any relevant log output.
      value: |
        <details>
        <summary>Log output</summary>

        ```sh
        Your log output
        ```
        </details>
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: textarea
    attributes:
      label: Potential fix
      description: |
        Tell us if you have an idea on what cause this installation problem or how to fix it.
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        Thanks for contributing üéâ!
